shape: sequence_diagram
vars: {
  d2-config: {
    # layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}
classes: {
  response: {
    style: {
      stroke-dash: 5
    }
  }
}
browser: {shape: person}
index_tsx: {label: index.tsx}
App
Redux: Redux store
connector: connector API
lichess: Lichess API
chesscom: Chess.com API

browser -> index_tsx: load page
index_tsx.note1: |md
  ```
  init Eruda mobile console
  createRoot(#root).render(<App />)
  ```
|
index_tsx -> App: render
App.note1: |md
  ```
  Redux Provider
  LichessGameProvider
  BrowserRouter
  route / → UnifiedChessContainer
  route /auth/callback → AuthCallback
  ```
|

App -> Redux: initialize store (positions, puzzles, setups slices)
App -> connector: "GET /none?fen_string=<starting FEN>"
connector -> App: "{nodes, edges:[]}" {class: response}
App.note2: |md
  ```
  render UnifiedChessContainer:
  control panels (Appearance, Setup, Moves)
  main view (board / graph / arc / chord / graphdag)
  history view (move table or metrics chart)
  ```
|

browser -> App: change connection type or FEN
App -> Redux: dispatch loadFen / setConnectionType
App -> connector: "GET /<endpoint>?fen_string=<FEN>"
connector -> App: "{nodes, edges}" {class: response}
App.note3: |md
  ```
  D3.js renders updated visualization
  URL params synced via useUrlSync hook
  ```
|

browser -> App: sign in with Lichess
App -> lichess: "redirect to /oauth (PKCE flow)"
lichess -> App: auth code → /auth/callback {class: response}
App -> lichess: "POST /api/token (exchange code)"
lichess -> App: access token {class: response}
App.note4: |md
  ```
  token stored in localStorage
  enables game streaming and challenges
  ```
|

browser -> App: load daily puzzle
App -> chesscom: "GET /pub/puzzle"
chesscom -> App: puzzle FEN + solution {class: response}
